freenet.keys
Class ClientKey

java.lang.Object
  freenet.keys.BaseClientKey
      freenet.keys.ClientKey
Direct Known Subclasses:
ClientCHK, ClientSSK
public abstract class ClientKey
extends BaseClientKey

Base class for client keys. Client keys are decodable. Node keys are not. When data has been fetched to a node-level KeyBlock, it can only be decoded after a ClientKeyBlock has been constructed from the node-level block and the client key. The client key generally contains the encryption keys which the node level does not know about, but which are in the URI - usually the second part, after the comma.
